					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7122598#post-3924566</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7122598/scp-3711#post-3924566</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 24 Aug 2018 14:56:28 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>DrBleep</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2887044</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Magic and the development of magic could, in its own right, be an anomaly unto itself. I am neither equipped, nor willing to broach magic under any single anomaly (we have several systems that try and I don't want to tread on that ground). I don't think <em>making</em> the development of magic an article would, in and of itself, be an altogether interesting concept, as this article exists within a headcanon space for me, as an author, where <em>anyone</em> can develop the ability to use magic through various means and ways, some of which are easily accessible, and some of which are very much not. That's not really a story I wanted to tell, nor do I think it would have been conducive to the pacing of the article as it is.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
